    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I propose to make a glossary more visible in cython documentation.\r\n\r\n## Rationale\r\n\r\nCython is using plenty of concepts which should be explained in single place -e. g.\r\n\r\n* cdef/@cfunc functions methods\r\n* cpdef/@ccall functions or methods\r\n* extention types / cdef classes\r\n* cdef statement\r\n* pyc files, pxd files ...\r\n* ...\r\n\r\nSee also the discussion here: https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4516#discussion_r799387386\r\n\r\nCurrently Glossary is hard to find and definitions are not linked to the glossary. It would be great to have more items in Glossary.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\nWe should do something similar what is python doing: https://docs.python.org/3/glossary.html. We should go over documentation pick up names and definition for each construct in cython, put it in glossary and create a links to it in documentation.\r\n",
